Note: Advanced Attention Mechanisms for AI Agents
Implements selective attention, spatial attention, temporal attention,
multi-head attention, transformer architectures, and attention flow
Competitive with Transformer, BERT, attention-based neural networks

Core attention types and structures :End Note
Type AttentionMechanism is Dictionary with:
    attention id as String
    attention name as String
    attention type as String  Note: "self_attention", "cross_attention", "multi_head", "spatial", "temporal"
    input dimension as Integer
    output dimension as Integer
    attention weights as Matrix
    attention scores as Matrix
    attention parameters as Dictionary[String, Float]
    computation complexity as String

Type AttentionHead is Dictionary with:
    head id as String
    head index as Integer
    query projection as Matrix
    key projection as Matrix
    value projection as Matrix
    attention dimension as Integer
    scaling factor as Float
    dropout rate as Float
    head weights as Matrix

Type AttentionContext is Dictionary with:
    context id as String
    input sequence as List[Vector]
    sequence length as Integer
    padding mask as List[Boolean]
    attention mask as Matrix
    position encodings as List[Vector]
    context embeddings as List[Vector]
    temporal markers as List[Integer]

Type SpatialAttention is Dictionary with:
    spatial attention id as String
    attention map as Matrix
    spatial dimensions as List[Integer]
    feature maps as List[Matrix]
    spatial weights as Matrix
    locality bias as Float
    attention radius as Integer
    spatial pooling as String

Type TemporalAttention is Dictionary with:
    temporal attention id as String
    time window as Integer
    temporal weights as Vector
    recency bias as Float
    temporal decay as Float
    sequence states as List[Vector]
    temporal patterns as List[Pattern]

Type AttentionFlow is Dictionary with:
    flow id as String
    attention layers as List[AttentionMechanism]
    layer connections as List[Connection]
    gradient flow as List[Vector]
    attention bottlenecks as List[String]
    information flow as Dictionary[String, Float]

Note: Multi-Head Attention Implementation
Process called "create_multi_head_attention" that takes config as Dictionary returns AttentionMechanism:
    Let attention be create_attention_mechanism_structure
    Set attention with field attention_id to generate_attention_id
    Set attention with field attention_name to config with key "name" or "Multi-Head Attention"
    Set attention with field attention_type to "multi_head"
    Set attention with field input_dimension to config with key "input_dim"
    Set attention with field output_dimension to config with key "output_dim" or config with key "input_dim"
    
    Let num_heads be config with key "num_heads" or 8
    Let head_dimension be attention with field input_dimension divided by num_heads
    
    Note: Create attention heads
    Let attention_heads be empty list
    For head_index from 0 to num_heads minus 1:
        Let head be create_attention_head_structure
        Set head with field head_id to generate_attention_head_id
        Set head with field head_index to head_index
        Set head with field attention_dimension to head_dimension
        Set head with field scaling_factor to 1.0 divided by square_root of head_dimension as Float
        Set head with field dropout_rate to config with key "dropout" or 0.1
        
        Note: Initialize projection matrices
        Set head with field query_projection to initialize_random_matrix with head_dimension and head_dimension
        Set head with field key_projection to initialize_random_matrix with head_dimension and head_dimension
        Set head with field value_projection to initialize_random_matrix with head_dimension and head_dimension
        
        Add head to attention_heads
    
    Set attention with field attention_parameters with key "heads" to attention_heads
    Set attention with field attention_parameters with key "num_heads" to num_heads
    Set attention with field attention_parameters with key "head_dimension" to head_dimension
    
    Return attention

Process called "apply_multi_head_attention" that takes attention as AttentionMechanism and context as AttentionContext returns Dictionary:
    Let result be empty dictionary
    Set result with key "attention_output" to empty list
    Set result with key "attention_weights" to empty list
    Set result with key "computation_stats" to empty dictionary
    
    Let input_sequence be context with field input_sequence
    Let sequence_length be context with field sequence_length
    Let attention_heads be attention with field attention_parameters with key "heads"
    
    Let head_outputs be empty list
    Let head_attention_weights be empty list
    
    Note: Process each attention head
    For each head in attention_heads:
        Let head_result be apply_single_attention_head with head and input_sequence and context
        
        Add head_result with key "head_output" to head_outputs
        Add head_result with key "attention_weights" to head_attention_weights
    
    Note: Concatenate head outputs
    Let concatenated_output be concatenate_attention_heads with head_outputs
    
    Note: Apply output projection
    Let output_projection be attention with field attention_parameters with key "output_projection"
    Let final_output be matrix_multiply with concatenated_output and output_projection
    
    Set result with key "attention_output" to final_output
    Set result with key "attention_weights" to head_attention_weights
    Set result with key "head_outputs" to head_outputs
    
    Return result

Process called "apply_single_attention_head" that takes head as AttentionHead and input_sequence as List[Vector] and context as AttentionContext returns Dictionary:
    Let head_result be empty dictionary
    
    Let query_projection be head with field query_projection
    Let key_projection be head with field key_projection
    Let value_projection be head with field value_projection
    Let scaling_factor be head with field scaling_factor
    
    Note: Apply projections to input sequence
    Let queries be empty list
    Let keys be empty list
    Let values be empty list
    
    For each input_vector in input_sequence:
        Let query be matrix_vector_multiply with query_projection and input_vector
        Let key be matrix_vector_multiply with key_projection and input_vector
        Let value be matrix_vector_multiply with value_projection and input_vector
        
        Add query to queries
        Add key to keys
        Add value to values
    
    Note: Compute attention scores
    Let attention_scores be compute_attention_scores with queries and keys and scaling_factor
    
    Note: Apply attention mask if provided
    If context contains field attention_mask:
        Set attention_scores to apply_attention_mask with attention_scores and context with field attention_mask
    
    Note: Apply softmax to get attention weights
    Let attention_weights be apply_softmax_to_matrix with attention_scores
    
    Note: Apply dropout if specified
    Let dropout_rate be head with field dropout_rate
    If dropout_rate is greater than 0.0:
        Set attention_weights to apply_dropout with attention_weights and dropout_rate
    
    Note: Compute weighted values
    Let head_output be compute_weighted_values with attention_weights and values
    
    Set head_result with key "head_output" to head_output
    Set head_result with key "attention_weights" to attention_weights
    Set head_result with key "attention_scores" to attention_scores
    
    Return head_result

Process called "compute_attention_scores" that takes queries as List[Vector] and keys as List[Vector] and scaling_factor as Float returns Matrix:
    Let sequence_length be length of queries
    Let attention_scores be create_matrix with sequence_length and sequence_length
    
    Note: Compute all pairwise attention scores
    For i from 0 to sequence_length minus 1:
        For j from 0 to sequence_length minus 1:
            Let query be queries with index i
            Let key be keys with index j
            
            Note: Compute dot product attention score
            Let dot_product be vector_dot_product with query and key
            Let scaled_score be dot_product multiplied by scaling_factor
            
            Set attention_scores with index i with index j to scaled_score
    
    Return attention_scores

Process called "compute_weighted_values" that takes attention_weights as Matrix and values as List[Vector] returns List[Vector]:
    Let sequence_length be length of values
    Let value_dimension be length of values with index 0
    Let weighted_output be empty list
    
    Note: Compute weighted sum for each position
    For i from 0 to sequence_length minus 1:
        Let weighted_value be create_vector with value_dimension filled with 0.0
        
        For j from 0 to sequence_length minus 1:
            Let weight be attention_weights with index i with index j
            Let value be values with index j
            
            Let weighted_contribution be scalar_vector_multiply with weight and value
            Set weighted_value to vector_add with weighted_value and weighted_contribution
        
        Add weighted_value to weighted_output
    
    Return weighted_output

Note: Self-Attention Mechanism
Process called "create_self_attention" that takes config as Dictionary returns AttentionMechanism:
    Let attention be create_attention_mechanism_structure
    Set attention with field attention_id to generate_attention_id
    Set attention with field attention_name to config with key "name" or "Self-Attention"
    Set attention with field attention_type to "self_attention"
    Set attention with field input_dimension to config with key "input_dim"
    Set attention with field output_dimension to config with key "input_dim"
    
    Let dimension be attention with field input_dimension
    
    Note: Initialize projection matrices for self-attention
    Let query_weights be initialize_random_matrix with dimension and dimension
    Let key_weights be initialize_random_matrix with dimension and dimension
    Let value_weights be initialize_random_matrix with dimension and dimension
    
    Set attention with field attention_parameters with key "query_weights" to query_weights
    Set attention with field attention_parameters with key "key_weights" to key_weights
    Set attention with field attention_parameters with key "value_weights" to value_weights
    Set attention with field attention_parameters with key "scaling_factor" to 1.0 divided by square_root of dimension as Float
    
    Return attention

Process called "apply_self_attention" that takes attention as AttentionMechanism and context as AttentionContext returns Dictionary:
    Let result be empty dictionary
    
    Let input_sequence be context with field input_sequence
    Let query_weights be attention with field attention_parameters with key "query_weights"
    Let key_weights be attention with field attention_parameters with key "key_weights"
    Let value_weights be attention with field attention_parameters with key "value_weights"
    Let scaling_factor be attention with field attention_parameters with key "scaling_factor"
    
    Note: Compute queries, keys, and values from same input
    Let queries be empty list
    Let keys be empty list
    Let values be empty list
    
    For each input_vector in input_sequence:
        Let query be matrix_vector_multiply with query_weights and input_vector
        Let key be matrix_vector_multiply with key_weights and input_vector
        Let value be matrix_vector_multiply with value_weights and input_vector
        
        Add query to queries
        Add key to keys
        Add value to values
    
    Note: Compute self-attention
    Let attention_scores be compute_attention_scores with queries and keys and scaling_factor
    Let attention_weights be apply_softmax_to_matrix with attention_scores
    Let attention_output be compute_weighted_values with attention_weights and values
    
    Set result with key "attention_output" to attention_output
    Set result with key "attention_weights" to attention_weights
    Set result with key "attention_scores" to attention_scores
    
    Return result

Note: Spatial Attention Mechanism
Process called "create_spatial_attention" that takes config as Dictionary returns SpatialAttention:
    Let spatial_attention be create_spatial_attention_structure
    Set spatial_attention with field spatial_attention_id to generate_spatial_attention_id
    Set spatial_attention with field spatial_dimensions to config with key "spatial_dims"
    Set spatial_attention with field attention_radius to config with key "radius" or 3
    Set spatial_attention with field locality_bias to config with key "locality_bias" or 1.0
    Set spatial_attention with field spatial_pooling to config with key "pooling" or "max"
    
    Let height be config with key "spatial_dims" with index 0
    Let width be config with key "spatial_dims" with index 1
    
    Note: Initialize spatial attention map
    Let attention_map be create_matrix with height and width filled with 1.0
    Set spatial_attention with field attention_map to attention_map
    
    Note: Initialize spatial weights with locality bias
    Let spatial_weights be create_spatial_weight_matrix with height and width and spatial_attention with field locality_bias
    Set spatial_attention with field spatial_weights to spatial_weights
    
    Return spatial_attention

Process called "apply_spatial_attention" that takes spatial_attention as SpatialAttention and feature_maps as List[Matrix] returns Dictionary:
    Let result be empty dictionary
    
    Let attention_map be spatial_attention with field attention_map
    Let spatial_weights be spatial_attention with field spatial_weights
    Let spatial_dimensions be spatial_attention with field spatial_dimensions
    Let attention_radius be spatial_attention with field attention_radius
    
    Let attended_features be empty list
    
    Note: Apply spatial attention to each feature map
    For each feature_map in feature_maps:
        Let attended_feature_map be apply_spatial_attention_to_map with feature_map and attention_map and spatial_weights and attention_radius
        Add attended_feature_map to attended_features
    
    Note: Compute attention statistics
    Let attention_entropy be calculate_spatial_attention_entropy with attention_map
    Let attention_sparsity be calculate_spatial_attention_sparsity with attention_map
    
    Set result with key "attended_features" to attended_features
    Set result with key "attention_map" to attention_map
    Set result with key "attention_entropy" to attention_entropy
    Set result with key "attention_sparsity" to attention_sparsity
    
    Return result

Process called "apply_spatial_attention_to_map" that takes feature_map as Matrix and attention_map as Matrix and spatial_weights as Matrix and radius as Integer returns Matrix:
    Let height be length of feature_map
    Let width be length of feature_map with index 0
    Let attended_map be create_matrix with height and width
    
    Note: Apply spatial attention with locality constraints
    For i from 0 to height minus 1:
        For j from 0 to width minus 1:
            Let attention_weight be attention_map with index i with index j
            Let spatial_weight be spatial_weights with index i with index j
            Let feature_value be feature_map with index i with index j
            
            Note: Apply local neighborhood attention
            Let neighborhood_sum be 0.0
            Let neighborhood_count be 0
            
            For di from negative radius to radius:
                For dj from negative radius to radius:
                    Let ni be i plus di
                    Let nj be j plus dj
                    
                    If ni is greater than or equal to 0 and ni is less than height and nj is greater than or equal to 0 and nj is less than width:
                        Let neighbor_attention be attention_map with index ni with index nj
                        Let neighbor_feature be feature_map with index ni with index nj
                        
                        Set neighborhood_sum to neighborhood_sum plus (neighbor_attention multiplied by neighbor_feature)
                        Set neighborhood_count to neighborhood_count plus 1
            
            Let local_attention be neighborhood_sum divided by neighborhood_count as Float
            Let final_attention be (attention_weight multiplied by feature_value) plus (spatial_weight multiplied by local_attention)
            
            Set attended_map with index i with index j to final_attention
    
    Return attended_map

Note: Temporal Attention Mechanism
Process called "create_temporal_attention" that takes config as Dictionary returns TemporalAttention:
    Let temporal_attention be create_temporal_attention_structure
    Set temporal_attention with field temporal_attention_id to generate_temporal_attention_id
    Set temporal_attention with field time_window to config with key "time_window" or 10
    Set temporal_attention with field recency_bias to config with key "recency_bias" or 0.9
    Set temporal_attention with field temporal_decay to config with key "temporal_decay" or 0.95
    
    Let time_window be temporal_attention with field time_window
    
    Note: Initialize temporal weights with recency bias
    let temporal_weights be create_vector with time_window
    Let recency_bias be temporal_attention with field recency_bias
    
    For t from 0 to time_window minus 1:
        Let recency_factor be power with base as recency_bias and exponent as (time_window minus 1 minus t)
        Set temporal_weights with index t to recency_factor
    
    Note: Normalize temporal weights
    Let weight_sum be sum_vector_elements with temporal_weights
    For t from 0 to time_window minus 1:
        Set temporal_weights with index t to temporal_weights with index t divided by weight_sum
    
    Set temporal_attention with field temporal_weights to temporal_weights
    Set temporal_attention with field sequence_states to empty list
    
    Return temporal_attention

Process called "apply_temporal_attention" that takes temporal_attention as TemporalAttention and sequence_states as List[Vector] returns Dictionary:
    Let result be empty dictionary
    
    Let temporal_weights be temporal_attention with field temporal_weights
    Let time_window be temporal_attention with field time_window
    Let temporal_decay be temporal_attention with field temporal_decay
    
    Let sequence_length be length of sequence_states
    Let state_dimension be length of sequence_states with index 0
    
    Let attended_sequence be empty list
    
    Note: Apply temporal attention to each time step
    For t from 0 to sequence_length minus 1:
        Let current_state be sequence_states with index t
        Let attended_state be create_vector with state_dimension filled with 0.0
        
        Note: Compute attention over time window
        Let window_start be maximum of 0 and (t minus time_window plus 1)
        
        For s from window_start to t:
            Let time_offset be t minus s
            If time_offset is less than time_window:
                Let temporal_weight be temporal_weights with index time_offset
                Let historical_state be sequence_states with index s
                
                Note: Apply temporal decay
                Let decay_factor be power with base as temporal_decay and exponent as time_offset
                Let decayed_weight be temporal_weight multiplied by decay_factor
                
                Let weighted_contribution be scalar_vector_multiply with decayed_weight and historical_state
                Set attended_state to vector_add with attended_state and weighted_contribution
        
        Add attended_state to attended_sequence
    
    Note: Compute temporal attention statistics
    Let temporal_focus be calculate_temporal_attention_focus with temporal_weights
    Let temporal_diversity be calculate_temporal_attention_diversity with temporal_weights
    
    Set result with key "attended_sequence" to attended_sequence
    Set result with key "temporal_weights" to temporal_weights
    Set result with key "temporal_focus" to temporal_focus
    Set result with key "temporal_diversity" to temporal_diversity
    
    Return result

Note: Cross-Attention Mechanism
Process called "create_cross_attention" that takes config as Dictionary returns AttentionMechanism:
    Let attention be create_attention_mechanism_structure
    Set attention with field attention_id to generate_attention_id
    Set attention with field attention_name to config with key "name" or "Cross-Attention"
    Set attention with field attention_type to "cross_attention"
    Set attention with field input_dimension to config with key "input_dim"
    Set attention with field output_dimension to config with key "output_dim" or config with key "input_dim"
    
    Let query_dim be config with key "query_dim" or config with key "input_dim"
    Let key_dim be config with key "key_dim" or config with key "input_dim"
    Let value_dim be config with key "value_dim" or config with key "input_dim"
    
    Note: Initialize projection matrices for cross-attention
    Let query_projection be initialize_random_matrix with query_dim and attention with field output_dimension
    Let key_projection be initialize_random_matrix with key_dim and attention with field output_dimension
    Let value_projection be initialize_random_matrix with value_dim and attention with field output_dimension
    
    Set attention with field attention_parameters with key "query_projection" to query_projection
    Set attention with field attention_parameters with key "key_projection" to key_projection
    Set attention with field attention_parameters with key "value_projection" to value_projection
    Set attention with field attention_parameters with key "scaling_factor" to 1.0 divided by square_root of attention with field output_dimension as Float
    
    Return attention

Process called "apply_cross_attention" that takes attention as AttentionMechanism and query_sequence as List[Vector] and key_value_sequence as List[Vector] returns Dictionary:
    Let result be empty dictionary
    
    Let query_projection be attention with field attention_parameters with key "query_projection"
    Let key_projection be attention with field attention_parameters with key "key_projection"
    Let value_projection be attention with field attention_parameters with key "value_projection"
    Let scaling_factor be attention with field attention_parameters with key "scaling_factor"
    
    Note: Project query sequence
    Let projected_queries be empty list
    For each query_vector in query_sequence:
        Let projected_query be matrix_vector_multiply with query_projection and query_vector
        Add projected_query to projected_queries
    
    Note: Project key and value sequences
    Let projected_keys be empty list
    Let projected_values be empty list
    
    For each kv_vector in key_value_sequence:
        Let projected_key be matrix_vector_multiply with key_projection and kv_vector
        Let projected_value be matrix_vector_multiply with value_projection and kv_vector
        
        Add projected_key to projected_keys
        Add projected_value to projected_values
    
    Note: Compute cross-attention scores
    Let cross_attention_scores be compute_cross_attention_scores with projected_queries and projected_keys and scaling_factor
    Let attention_weights be apply_softmax_to_matrix with cross_attention_scores
    Let attention_output be compute_weighted_values with attention_weights and projected_values
    
    Set result with key "attention_output" to attention_output
    Set result with key "attention_weights" to attention_weights
    Set result with key "cross_attention_scores" to cross_attention_scores
    
    Return result

Process called "compute_cross_attention_scores" that takes queries as List[Vector] and keys as List[Vector] and scaling_factor as Float returns Matrix:
    Let query_length be length of queries
    Let key_length be length of keys
    Let attention_scores be create_matrix with query_length and key_length
    
    Note: Compute cross-attention scores between queries and keys
    For i from 0 to query_length minus 1:
        For j from 0 to key_length minus 1:
            Let query be queries with index i
            Let key be keys with index j
            
            Let dot_product be vector_dot_product with query and key
            Let scaled_score be dot_product multiplied by scaling_factor
            
            Set attention_scores with index i with index j to scaled_score
    
    Return attention_scores

Note: Attention Visualization and Analysis
Process called "analyze_attention_patterns" that takes attention_weights as Matrix and sequence_info as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let analysis be empty dictionary
    
    Note: Calculate attention entropy
    Let attention_entropy be calculate_attention_entropy with attention_weights
    Set analysis with key "attention_entropy" to attention_entropy
    
    Note: Calculate attention sparsity
    Let attention_sparsity be calculate_attention_sparsity with attention_weights
    Set analysis with key "attention_sparsity" to attention_sparsity
    
    Note: Find attention peaks
    Let attention_peaks be find_attention_peaks with attention_weights
    Set analysis with key "attention_peaks" to attention_peaks
    
    Note: Calculate attention alignment
    If sequence_info contains key "reference_alignment":
        Let reference_alignment be sequence_info with key "reference_alignment"
        Let attention_alignment_score be calculate_attention_alignment with attention_weights and reference_alignment
        Set analysis with key "alignment_score" to attention_alignment_score
    
    Note: Analyze attention distribution
    Let attention_statistics be calculate_attention_statistics with attention_weights
    Set analysis with key "attention_statistics" to attention_statistics
    
    Return analysis

Process called "calculate_attention_entropy" that takes attention_weights as Matrix returns Float:
    Let total_entropy be 0.0
    Let num_positions be length of attention_weights
    
    For i from 0 to num_positions minus 1:
        Let position_entropy be 0.0
        
        For j from 0 to length of attention_weights with index i minus 1:
            Let weight be attention_weights with index i with index j
            
            If weight is greater than 0.0:
                Set position_entropy to position_entropy minus (weight multiplied by logarithm_base_2 of weight)
        
        Set total_entropy to total_entropy plus position_entropy
    
    Return total_entropy divided by num_positions as Float

Note: Main attention system coordination
Process called "create_attention_system" that takes configuration as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let system be empty dictionary
    Set system with key "attention_mechanisms" to configuration with key "mechanisms" or list containing "self_attention", "multi_head", "spatial", "temporal"
    Set system with key "attention_visualization" to configuration with key "visualization" or true
    Set system with key "attention_analysis" to configuration with key "analysis" or true
    Set system with key "gradient_computation" to configuration with key "gradients" or true
    Set system with key "attention_optimization" to configuration with key "optimization" or false
    
    Return system

Process called "execute_attention_analysis" that takes system as Dictionary and query as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let query_type be query with key "type"
    Let result be empty dictionary
    
    If query_type is equal to "apply_multi_head_attention":
        Let attention_config be query with key "attention_config"
        Let context be query with key "context"
        
        Let attention_mechanism be create_multi_head_attention with attention_config
        Let attention_result be apply_multi_head_attention with attention_mechanism and context
        Set result with key "attention_result" to attention_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "apply_self_attention":
        Let attention_config be query with key "attention_config"
        Let context be query with key "context"
        
        Let attention_mechanism be create_self_attention with attention_config
        Let attention_result be apply_self_attention with attention_mechanism and context
        Set result with key "attention_result" to attention_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "apply_spatial_attention":
        Let spatial_config be query with key "spatial_config"
        Let feature_maps be query with key "feature_maps"
        
        Let spatial_attention be create_spatial_attention with spatial_config
        Let spatial_result be apply_spatial_attention with spatial_attention and feature_maps
        Set result with key "spatial_attention_result" to spatial_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "apply_temporal_attention":
        Let temporal_config be query with key "temporal_config"
        Let sequence_states be query with key "sequence_states"
        
        Let temporal_attention be create_temporal_attention with temporal_config
        Let temporal_result be apply_temporal_attention with temporal_attention and sequence_states
        Set result with key "temporal_attention_result" to temporal_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "apply_cross_attention":
        Let attention_config be query with key "attention_config"
        Let query_sequence be query with key "query_sequence"
        Let key_value_sequence be query with key "key_value_sequence"
        
        Let cross_attention be create_cross_attention with attention_config
        Let cross_result be apply_cross_attention with cross_attention and query_sequence and key_value_sequence
        Set result with key "cross_attention_result" to cross_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "analyze_attention":
        Let attention_weights be query with key "attention_weights"
        Let sequence_info be query with key "sequence_info"
        
        Let analysis_result be analyze_attention_patterns with attention_weights and sequence_info
        Set result with key "attention_analysis" to analysis_result
    
    Note: Add metadata
    Set result with key "attention_timestamp" to current_timestamp
    Set result with key "system_config" to extract_system_summary with system
    
    Return result